definition: Slovakia/Slovak/abbr. for 斯洛伐克[Si1 luo4 fa2 ke4]
Serbia/Serbian/abbr. for 塞爾維亞|塞尔维亚[Sai1 er3 wei2 ya4]
to stop up/to squeeze in/to stuff/cork/stopper
to stop up/to stuff/to cope with

sentences.english: However, he was registered at the Indian Creek School in Tunica as Robert Spencer.
sentences.chinese: 然而，他註冊丘尼卡羅伯特斯賓塞在印度河學校。

sentences.english: Watch Spencer's video at Vimeo here.
sentences.chinese: 點擊觀看斯賓塞的視頻。

sentences.english: Byron quite casually said that he had 'a lot of Spenserian stanzas'.
sentences.chinese: 拜倫漫不經心地說，寫了“許多斯賓塞詩節”。

sentences.english: Spencer family is one of the richest merchants of sheep in Europe in the 15th century.
sentences.chinese: 斯賓塞家族是15世紀歐洲最富有的羊商之一。

sentences.english: I was reading an essay by Saleeby on Spencer.
sentences.chinese: 讀到了一篇撒裏比論斯賓塞的文章。

sentences.english: Boy, I rang that doorbell fast when I got to old Spencer's house.
sentences.chinese: 嘿，我一到老斯賓塞家門口，就拼命按起鈴來。

sentences.english: Norrine Bailey Spencer is the associate provost and director of undergraduate admissions.
sentences.chinese: 勞瑞拉貝雷斯賓塞是負責本科招生的協理主任。

sentences.english: Even the stanchest of Spencer's followers will not go farther.
sentences.chinese: 即使斯賓塞的最堅強的信徒也難於再前進了。

sentences.english: But Spencer Tracy remained the love of her life.
sentences.chinese: 但斯賓塞特蕾西仍然愛她的生活。

sentences.english: Frontier Journal is interviewing Professor Michael Spence at Stanford University.
sentences.chinese: 前沿雜誌是面試教授邁克爾斯賓塞在斯坦福大學。
